SIMPLE: therewithal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Therewithal
<hw>There`with*al"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Over and above; besides; moreover.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Daniel.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>therewithal</qex> it was full poor and bad.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>With that or this; therewith; at the same
time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy slanders I forgive; and <qex>therewithal</qex>⟦br⟧
Remit thy other forfeits.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>therewithal</qex> one came and seized on her,⟦br⟧
And Enid started waking.</q> <rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Therf</ent>⟦br⟧
